Preheat your oven to 200°C. Boil a half-full #kettle{}. Chop the @sweet potato{2}(cut into 2cm wide wedges, no need to peel). Zest and halve the @lime{1/2}. Put the @peanut butter{60%g}, @soy sauce{15%ml}, @sweet chilli sauce{48%ml} and @boiling water{2} into a #bowl{}. Squeeze in half the lime juice and mix to combine. Set aside.

> TIP: Add another splash of water if you feel it needs it - you want it drizzling consistency.

Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil, season with @salt and @pepper then sprinkle over the @sesame seeds{7%g}. Toss to coat then spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the middle shelf until golden, ~{30-40%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Pop the @panko breadcrumbs{10%g} into a bowl. Add the @red Thai style paste{50%g} and lime zest then mix together. Add the @British pork mince{240%g}. Season with salt and pepper. Using your hands, mix everything together until very well combined. Shape the mixture into evenly sized balls, 5 per person.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the meatballs onto another large baking tray, drizzle with oil then bake on the top shelf of your oven until browned on the outside and cooked through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The meatballs are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @salted peanuts{25%g} and pop into a medium bowl. Squeeze in the remaining lime juice and add the @olive oil{1.5%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with salt, pepper and a pinch of @sugar. Mix to combine.

Trim and peel the @carrot{2}, then trim the @cucumber{1/2}. Use a #vegetable peeler{} to peel long ribbons from all sides of the lengths of both. Stop when you get to the core/seeds. Pick the @mint{1}(leaves picked from stalks, stalks discarded) and roughly chop. Add the mint to the bowl of dressing and mix again, then add the carrot and cucumber ribbons. Toss to coat in the dressing.

When everything has nearly finished cooking, pop the @Greek style flatbreads{2} in your oven until warm and starting to turn golden, ~{3-4%minutes}. Serve the flatbreads with a handful of salad on top, followed by the meatballs and some peanut butter drizzle. Divide the sweet potato wedges between your plates with any remaining salad and peanut sauce on the side. Enjoy!